    <h1>Upholding Human Dignity and Human Rights</h1>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Upholding Human Dignity and Human Rights as an important part of Peace Education. Human dignity means that every person has value and deserves respect simply because they are human. Because of this dignity, everyone is entitled to basic rights that protect their freedom, safety, and well-being. After the tragedies of World War II, the United Nations created the Universal Declaration of Human Rights in 1948 to protect the rights and dignity of all people. Understanding these rights helps us build a more peaceful, fair, and respectful society.</p>

